blockchain.\r\n\r\nConcurrently, a \"DRM computer system would verify the rights in the blockchain and then decrypt the media when needed. This computer system can take different forms, including a \"DRM agent\" residing on a user\'s device, according to Sony.\r\n\r\nAs previously reported, Sony has been looking at other applications of the technology, including as a means to <a href=\"https://www.coindesk.com/sony-seeks-blockchain-patent-for-user-authentication-system/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">authenticate user data</a> and <a href=\"https://www.coindesk.com/sony-patent-filing-details-blockchain-use-managing-education-data/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">manage education data</a>.\r\n\r\n<i>Image Credit: <a href=\"https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/beijing-china-april-24-2016-sony-437436343?src=NUeHwakF9Q_kLO_fnKy2jg-1-78\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">testing / Shutterstock.com</a></i>'),
